name: Medusae - a bloom of Pelagia Noctiluca
description: What can jellyfish teach us about climate change? Warming of temperatures, oxygen depletion and ocean acidification, coupled with overfishing and invasive species, are giving jellyfish advantage over other marine life. Pelagia Noctiluca, also called the Mauve Stinger, is a purple looking - glowing in the dark - jellyfish with a sting youâ€™ll remember.
